<p><h2><strong>A small rose leaf</strong> picked up in <strong>1984</strong> inspired the founders of Life-Link to use it as <strong>the symbol</strong> for this global peace programme for youth and schools worldwide. <strong>The green leaf symbolises life in several ways</strong>; the green chlorophyll as a biologically fundamental catalyst, plants as necessary links between organic and inorganic life and flowers as an inspiration for art, poetry, and music.</h2></p>

<p>Feel free to use the Life-Link leaf logo whenever you perform a Peace Action.</p>

